{
  "texts": [
    "To demonstrate its generalization on LLM servers, we also explore other different LLMs, including classic LLM (BERTfoot_4 [7]) and cutting-edge techniques (Llama3.1 5 and Llama2foot_6 [44]), in Section 5.9.",
    "We utilize item titles as the main input for LLMs.For the sequence representation service, we use the prefix \"The user's purchase history list is as follows:\" as the prompt.",
    "More complex prompts and additional item meta-information can be explored in future research.",
    "The last layer's hidden vector of the start special token is used as the embedding vector.Note that when investigating RQ2 to RQ5, we utilize SASRec as the base model by default, and we use FELLAS or FedSeqRec to directly refer to FELLAS(SASRec) or FedSeqRec(SASRec) respectively for concise presentation.",
    "The recommendation performance trend (HR@20) of FELLAS with different privacy parameter 𝜖 on three datasets."
  ]
}